theorem closure_interior_eq_self_of_P3_closed
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) :
    Topology.P3 (A : Set X) → closure (interior A) = A := by
  intro hP3
  -- From `P3`, we obtain `A ⊆ interior A` because `A` is closed.
  have hSub₁ : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior A := by
    have h := hP3
    simpa [hA_closed.closure_eq] using h
  -- The interior is always contained in the set itself.
  have hSub₂ : interior A ⊆ (A : Set X) := interior_subset
  -- Hence, `interior A = A`.
  have hIntEq : interior A = A := Set.Subset.antisymm hSub₂ hSub₁
  -- Taking closures yields the desired equality.
  have hClosEq : closure (interior A) = A := by
    have h' : closure (interior A) = closure A := by
      simpa using congrArg closure hIntEq
    simpa [hA_closed.closure_eq] using h'
  exact hClosEq

theorem closure_interior_closure_interior_subset_closure_interior_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (closure (interior (A : Set X)))) ⊆
      closure (interior (closure A)) := by
  exact
    closure_mono
      (Topology.interior_closure_interior_subset_closure (A := A))
